PBTC uses the Go standard libraries:

	* LICENSE:
		* license/LICENSE_go
	* WEBSITE:
		* http://go.googlesource.com/go/


PBTC uses btcd, an alternative full node bitcoin implementation written in Go (golang):

	* LICENSE:
		* license/LICENSE_btcd
	* WEBSITE:
		* http://github.com/btcsuite/btcutil


PBTC uses btcutil, which provides bitcoin-specific convenience functions and types:

	* LICENSE:
		* license/LICENSE_btcutil
	* WEBSITE:
		* http://github.com/btcsuite/btcd


PBTC uses go-logging, a Golang logging library:

	* LICENSE:
		* license/LICENSE_go-logging
	* WEBSITE:
		* http://github.com/op/go-logging


PBTC uses go-clz4, LZ4 (de)compression bindings to the C library found at http://code.google.com/p/lz4/:

	* LICENSE:
		* license/LICENSE_go-clz4
	* WEBSITE:
		* http://github.com/pwaller/go-clz4


PBTC uses pebbe zmq4, a Go interface to ZeroMQ version 4:

	* LICENSE:
		* license/LICENSE_zmq4
	* WEBSITE:
		* http://github.com/pebbe/zmq4


PBTC uses go-redis, the redis client for Golang:

	* LICENSE:
		* license/LICENSE_go-redis
	* WEBSITE:
		* http://github.com/go-redis
		

PBTC uses gcfg, a Go library that reads text-based configuration files that consist of "name=value" pairs grouped into sections:

	* LICENSE:
		* license/LICENSE_gcfg
	* WEBSITE:
		* http://code.google.com/p/gcfg